PP64 -- Bidirectional 8-bit Parallel Data Transfer between PS/2
Parallel Port and C64 User Port with optional reset circuit

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Introduction
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

...

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Cable
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a simple 8-bit parallel transfer cable connecting the PC
Parallel Port to the C64 User port.

The INIT line may be connected to an additional reset circuit that
grounds the C64's RESET line via a relay when INIT is pulled low.

---------------------------------------------
PC Parallel Port   |     C64 User Port
---------------------------------------------
GND    (18-25)    <->    GND    (1, 12, A, N)
D0     (2)        <->    PB0    (C) 
D1     (3)        <->    PB1    (D) 
D2     (4)        <->    PB2    (E) 
D3     (5)        <->    PB3    (F) 
D4     (6)        <->    PB4    (H) 
D5     (7)        <->    PB5    (J) 
D6     (8)        <->    PB6    (K) 
D7     (9)        <->    PB7    (L) 
BUSY   (11)       <--    PA2    (M) 
STROBE (1)        -->    /FLAG2 (B) 
INIT   (16)       -->   (Reset circuit) 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Reset Circuit
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                      +5V
                        o
          ____       | /                                                    
/INIT o--|____|---o--|<  T1
           R1        |\                 T1 = 2N2907   Transistor
                     | \                U1 = MES1A05  Relay
                        |               D1 = 1N296    Diode
                     ---o o--- /RES     R1 = 4.7kOhm  Resistor
                     |  | |                                             
                     -  ( |                                             
                 D1  ^  ( | U1                                            
                     |  | |                                           
                     ---o o                                             
                        \ /                                             
                         o                                              
                         GND                                            
                                                                        

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 

